<s> img alt="purple line" .  </s>
<s> While designing for access, it's important to consider the sighted viewers too!  </s>
<s> I see three audiences for the alt text: graphic browser users with image loading turned off, text browser users, and visually impaired users.  </s>
<s> Those with image loading turned off want to know whether to load the image.  </s>
<s> For them, an indication of whether or not a line is interesting enough to load is worthwhile.  </s>
<s> But for text browser users, a snippet of text doesn't have the same effect as a rule does - it doesn't break up the page in the same way.  </s>
<s> Using ASCII-graphic alt text helps them.  </s>
<s> And I think that most screen readers skip most punctuation.  </s>
<s> I think a combination alt text would work well for all three audiences: maybe something like img alt="purple line________________________________" and img alt="zig-zag line /\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\" would work well.  </s>
<s> I would use ALT as replacement text, TITLE as an image title: If we treat these attributes this way, we get simplicity and consistency.  </s>
